Root Cause Analysis
Primary root cause identified as unstable residential mains voltage delivery.
Contributing Factors:
• Absence of surge protection
• No voltage regulation
• Direct wall-socket connection
• Limitations of historical electrical installation
Voltage fluctuations likely resulted in:
• Capacitor damage
• Motherboard degradation
• PSU stress and internal instability
• Random system state corruption

