Resolution Steps
	1. Assessed residential electrical stability risk
	2. Purchased and installed UPS with integrated AVR, surge protection, and external voltage stabilizer
	3. Determined separate servo stabilizer not strictly required due to UPS AVR integration; however, retained as additional safety layer
	4. Connected all desktop systems through upgraded sockets, surge protector, AVR, and UPS
	5. Standardized use of high-quality power supplies only
	6. Monitored system behavior under sustained load conditions

