Lessons Learned
• PSU degradation may manifest as random freezing without BSOD
• Electrical instability can closely mimic hardware failure
• Bench testing without real-world power conditions may not reproduce issues
• Stepwise component replacement without infrastructure assessment significantly increases cost

Preventive Recommendations
• Always deploy AVR-enabled UPS for high-performance desktop systems
• Validate electrical stability before replacing core components
• Avoid assuming motherboard or CPU failure without PSU validation
• Conduct extended load testing before declaring system stable
• Operate all desktop systems behind AVR-enabled UPS
• Modernize electrical infrastructure where necessary
• Avoid direct wall-outlet operation for high-performance systems
• Perform periodic UPS battery health verification
